# Copy this file to `.env` in the same folder (FRONTEND/) and fill in real values.
# Never commit `.env` — it is listed in `.gitignore`.
# After editing `.env`, restart the dev server (Vite reads env at startup).
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# CHATBOT (POST /api/chat) — local dev + Vercel serverless
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# REQUIRED — at least one LLM key (server reads process.env; do NOT use VITE_ for secrets):
#   GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_...                    https://console.groq.com/keys
#   — OR for Gemini only (any one of these names is OK on the server):
#   GEMINI_API_KEY=...  OR  GOOGLE_AI_API_KEY=...  OR  reuse VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY below
#
# RECOMMENDED — signed-in profile + RLS in chat (same values as VITE_*; chat falls back to them):
#   VITE_SUPABASE_URL + VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
#   (Optional duplicates if you prefer non-VITE names in server-only env: SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_ANON_KEY)
#
# OPTIONAL
#   LLM_PROVIDER=auto|groq|gemini   (auto: Groq if GROQ_API_KEY is set, else Gemini if a Gemini key is set)
#   GROQ_MODEL=...                  Groq model id
#   GEMINI_CHAT_MODEL=...           e.g. gemini-2.0-flash
#   ALPHA_VANTAGE_KEY=...           delayed ticker hints in chat (not required for a reply)
#
# Vercel: add the same names under Project → Settings → Environment Variables (GROQ_API_KEY without VITE_).
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# REST OF APP (browser)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# If you see "Cannot reach Supabase": Dashboard → Project Settings → API (same project for both lines).

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT_REF.supabase.co
# Legacy anon JWT (eyJ...) or newer publishable key (sb_publishable_...) — both work with createClient
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=sb_publishable_...OR_eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIs...
# Copy to `.env` in this folder (never commit real keys).
# Alpha Vantage: https://www.alphavantage.co/support/#api-key
# Dashboard live stocks + news + symbol search use Finnhub if set, otherwise Alpha Vantage (either key is enough).
VITE_ALPHA_VANTAGE_API_KEY=

# Google AI (Gemini): https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=

# --- Paste chat LLM keys here (uncomment). See CHATBOT section at top of this file. ---
# GROQ_API_KEY=
# GEMINI_API_KEY=
# LLM_PROVIDER=auto

# Optional: Finnhub (quotes, news, search). If set, it is preferred over Alpha Vantage for those features.
# On Vercel, add either name — both are supported after build:
#   VITE_FINNHUB_API_KEY=...   (recommended; Vite default)
#   FINNHUB_API_KEY=...        (also works; exposed via envPrefix in vite.config)
# After changing env vars on Vercel, redeploy — Vite bakes them in at build time.
# VITE_FINNHUB_API_KEY=

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# CERTIFICATE VERIFICATION (FinvestCertRegistry on-chain registry)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# When users click "Verify on chain" on a profile certificate, the SPA POSTs the
# cert to /api/cert-issue, which (idempotently) publishes its keccak256 hash to
# the FinvestCertRegistry contract. The /verify page then re-hashes the cert
# client-side and reads the contract to prove it was issued by Finvest.
#
# Auto local setup (free, runs entirely on your machine):
#   cd blockchain && npm install && npm run cert:auto-local
# Then paste a prefunded Hardhat private key as CERT_ISSUER_PRIVATE_KEY below.
#
# Browser-readable (used by the /verify page and the issuer button):
# VITE_CERT_REGISTRY_ADDRESS=0x...
# VITE_CERT_REGISTRY_RPC_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8545
#
# Server-only (used by /api/cert-issue to sign the issuance transaction).
# These can be the same values as the VITE_* pair; the private key MUST stay server-side.
# CERT_REGISTRY_ADDRESS=0x...
# CERT_REGISTRY_RPC_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8545
# CERT_ISSUER_PRIVATE_KEY=0x...
